{{Taxobox | name = Maltese skate | image = | status = CR | status_system = IUCN3.1 | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Chordata]] | classis = [[Chondrichthyes]] | ordo = [[Rajiformes]] | familia = [[Rajidae]] | genus = ''[[Leucoraja]]'' | species = '''''L. melitensis''''' | binomial = ''Leucoraja melitensis'' | binomial_authority = ([[Robert Clark (zoologist)|R. S. Clark]], 1926) | synonyms = }}
The '''Maltese skate''' or '''Maltese ray''' (''Leucoraja melitensis'') is a species of [[fish]] in the [[Rajidae]] family. It is found in [[Algeria]], [[Italy]], [[Malta]], and [[Tunisia]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is open seas. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].
== Sustainable consumption == In 2010, [[Greenpeace|Greenpeace International]] added the Maltese skate (''Leucoraja melitensis'') to its seafood red list. "The Greenpeace International seafood red list is a list of fish that are commonly sold in supermarkets around the world, and which have a very high risk of being sourced from unsustainable fisheries."<ref>[http://www.greenpeace.org/international/en/campaigns/oceans/seafood/red-list-of-species/ Greenpeace International Seafood Red list]</ref>
