{{Chinese name|[[Zhuang (surname)|Zhuang]]}} [[File:Zhuang Yunkuan.jpg|200px|right]] [[File:Zhuang Yunkuan1.jpg|200px|right]] '''Zhuang Yunkuan''' ({{zh|莊蘊寬}}; 1867–1932), [[courtesy name]] Sijian ({{zh|思缄}}), art name Baohong ({{zh|抱闳}}), was a Chinese calligrapher and [[Qing dynasty]] and [[Republic of China (1912–49)|Republic of China]] politician. He was born in Wujin County, Changzhou Prefecture, [[Jiangsu]] (modern [[Wujin District]], [[Changzhou]]).<ref name=np>谢巍，中国历代人物年谱考录，北京：中华书局，1992年，第633页</ref> He was prefect of [[Pingnan County, Guangxi]], Sicheng (in [[Lingyun County]]) and [[Wuzhou]].<ref name=yf>约法会议秘书厅编，约法会议记录，北京：约法会议秘书厅，1915年，第80页</ref><ref name=cz>[http://www.gxczzx.com/wscq/58091.shtml 辛亥历史印记在龙州，崇左政协网，2011-10-15] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130626134403/http://www.gxczzx.com/wscq/58091.shtml |date=June 26, 2013 }}</ref><ref>蔡锷集，长沙：湖南人民出版社，1983年，第42页</ref> He was a delegate to the conference to create a provisional constitution for the Republic of China. In 1925, he served on the board of directors for the [[National Palace Museum]].<ref name="xhgmw">{{cite web|url=http://www.xhgmw.org/archive-54600.shtml |title= 庄研，故宫博物院对庄蕴宽的一份珍贵的评价，辛亥革命网，2011年06月17日 |publisher=xhgmw.org|accessdate=2016-03-15}}</ref><ref>江蘇省通誌稿（2），南京：江蘇古籍出版社，1993年</ref>
==Relatives== *[[Wu Zuguang]]: grandnephew<ref name="worldwu">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldwu.com/Article/Print.asp?ArticleID=2828 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304100126/http://www.worldwu.com/Article/Print.asp?ArticleID=2828 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |dead-url=yes |title= 吴欢，吴氏三代贞石良友，华夏吴氏网，2008-12-2 |accessdate=2016-03-15}}</ref>
